remained strong and
were level with 2012. renewal premium changes remained positive in 2013 and were slightly higher than in 2012, primarily due to higher renewal rate increases. new business premiums in 2013 declined
from 2012. net written premiums of $2.78billion in 2012 were virtually level with 2011. business retention rates in 2012 remained strong but were lower than in 2011. renewal premium changes
remained positive in 2012 and were higher than in 2011, primarily due to higher renewal rate increases. new business premiums in 2012 decreased from 2011. net written premiums in both 2013 and 2012
were favorably impacted by positive audit premium adjustments.
