premiums of $907million in 2012 increased by 16% over 2011. business retention rates remained strong in 2012 and were level with 2011. renewal premium changes were positive and were higher
than in 2011, driven by payroll exposure growth. new business premiums in 2012 increased over 2011. growth in workers' compensation residual market pools also contributed to premium growth in both
2013 and 2012.
