the company has entered into certain contingent obligations for guarantees related to the sale of business entities, certain
investments, third-party loans related to certain investments, certain insurance policy obligations of former insurance subsidiaries and various other indemnifications. see note16 of notes to
the company's consolidated financial statements. the company does not expect these arrangements will have a material effect on the company's financial position, changes in financial position, revenues
and expenses, results of operations, liquidity, capital expenditures or capital resources.
